---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import MainLayout from '@layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Divider from '@components/Divider.astro';
import labImage from '@assets/emma-jussi-labra.jpg';
import { paths } from '@data/paths';

const title = 'About us';
const description =
  'Clouder is on a mission to unlock the hidden value in real estate portfolios. We replace silos and fragmented operations with investment-grade data and turn it into measurable asset value.';
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section>
    <div class="pt-16 pb-8 lg:pt-32 lg:pb-16">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="lg:max-w-2/3">
          <h1
            class="mb-4 text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight text-neutral-950 lg:mb-8 lg:text-6xl dark:text-neutral-50"
          >
            Unlocking hidden value in real estate portfolios
          </h1>
          <p class="text-blance text-lg">{description}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container px-0">
      <Image
        src={labImage}
        alt="People in hardware laboratory"
        class="aspect-video bg-neutral-500/10 object-cover object-top text-transparent"
        width={1280}
        layout="constrained"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="py-16 lg:py-32">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-x-8">
          <h2
            class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-neutral-950 lg:row-span-2 lg:text-4xl dark:text-neutral-50"
          >
            Turning building data into asset intelligence
          </h2>
          <p class="text-balance">
            We have been on the other side of this problem. As real estate investors, owners, and
            asset managers, we have sat through the transactions, reviewed the reports, and managed
            the portfolios. And we kept seeing the same thing: assets that should be consuming less
            energy and performing better. Every wasted euro is permanently off the asset value. So
            we decided to build what the industry was missing.
          </p>
          <p class="text-balance">
            We built a direct connection to building systems (not through cloud APIs, but at the
            source) that turns real building data into real operational value. Clouder doesn't just
            read data. It acts on it, in real time, and learns from the result. Every building gets
            smarter, consumes less energy, and produces fewer emissions. Every new asset benefits
            from what we have already learned across the portfolio. The system compounds.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Divider />
  <section>
    <div class="py-16 lg:py-32">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-x-8">
          <h2
            class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-neutral-950 lg:row-span-2 lg:text-4xl dark:text-neutral-50"
          >
            Built by people who know commercial real estate and technology
          </h2>
          <p class="text-balance">
            Clouder is built on an uncommon combination of expertise: decades of experience in
            large-scale commercial real estate development, transactions and institutional asset
            management, paired with deep knowledge in data architecture, real-time systems
            engineering and enterprise-scale technology infrastructure. That breadth of competence
            across both disciplines is what makes it possible to build something the industry has
            not seen before.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Divider />
  <section>
    <div class="py-16 lg:py-32">
      <div class="container-narrow space-y-4 text-center lg:space-y-6">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-neutral-950 lg:row-span-2 lg:text-4xl dark:text-neutral-50"
        >
          The gap is measurable.<br />So is closing it.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-balance">
          Clouder works with commercial real estate funds, asset managers, and large-scale investors
          who manage portfolios where operational inefficiency has real, measurable consequences. If
          you suspect the gap between your portfolio's current value and its potential is larger
          than it should be, we should talk.
        </p>
        <div>
          <a
            href={paths.contact.href}
            class="mt-1 inline-flex h-10 cursor-pointer items-center justify-center gap-1 rounded bg-neutral-950 px-4 text-center text-sm font-medium text-nowrap text-neutral-50 transition select-none hover:bg-neutral-800 active:bg-neutral-800 dark:bg-neutral-50 dark:text-neutral-950 dark:hover:bg-neutral-200 dark:active:bg-neutral-200"
          >
            Get in touch
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
